OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30404
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1777306270
OL,3,CMore than 100 children's toys recalled
OL,4,Cover asbestos risk since January
OL,6,FAsbestos is a banned substance because
OL,7,Fit poses a health risk and can cause
OL,8,Fcancer, even at low levels of exposure.
OL,10,FIf a customer discovers they've bought
OL,11,Fand opened the sand in an impacted
OL,12,Fproduct, the Office for Product Safety
OL,13,Fand Standards (OPSS) recommends
OL,14,Fcleaning it with a wet cloth to avoid
OL,15,Fcreating dust, and double-bagging it,
OL,16,Fwearing gloves and a mask.
OL,18,FThe product should then be placed in a
OL,19,Fheavy-duty plastic bag and double-
OL,20,Ftaped securely, it said.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30405
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1777306270
OL,3,CMore than 100 children's toys recalled
OL,4,Cover asbestos risk since January
OL,6,FIt should then be returned to the
OL,7,Fplace of purchase for compensation,
OL,8,Fbut if this is not possible, the OPSS
OL,9,Fadvises throwing it away among
OL,10,Fhousehold waste.
OL,12,F"It is shocking that deadly asbestos
OL,13,Fis once again being found in
OL,14,Fchildren's toys sold at major
OL,15,Fretailers," Sue Davies, head of
OL,16,Fconsumer protection policy at Which?
OL,17,Fsaid.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30406
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1777306270
OL,3,CMore than 100 children's toys recalled
OL,4,Cover asbestos risk since January
OL,6,F"This points to serious failures in
OL,7,Fproduct safety checks. Manufacturers
OL,8,Fand retailers must urgently review
OL,9,Ftheir supplier oversight and testing
OL,10,Fto make sure unsafe products are not
OL,11,Freaching stores in the first place.
OL,13,F"The Office for Product Safety and
OL,14,FStandards needs to take action and
OL,15,Fensure proper checks are being carried
OL,16,Fout to keep dangerous products off the
OL,17,Fshelves.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
